<FMtopic>
<Title>
<?FTID-xref 1736707.0-00-01-00_FAA?>Document Content and Organization</Title>
<Para>The MEL is divided into five sections as follows:</Para>
<Para>SECTION 0 - GENERAL</Para>
<Para>SECTION 1 - EICAS MESSAGES</Para>
<Para>This section provides a cross reference between EICAS messages and MEL items which may provide dispatch relief.  The EICAS message list is in alphabetic order and includes all of the current EICAS messages.  The EICAS messages applicable to an operator’s airplane and the description of the condition or fault indicated by the messages can be found in the operator’s Fault
Isolation Manual (FIM).</Para>
<Para />
<Para>SECTION 2 - MEL</Para>
<Para>This section contains all items from the FAA MMEL.  For ease of use, page numbering uses the MEL item number as follows:</Para>
<GraphicSet id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.GR.0-00-01-00.1672864.0-00-01-00_FAA">
<Illustration fileRef="G0-00-01-00_FAA.fm_3178" linkRef="URN:X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.NX.GR.0-00-01-00.3178." />
</GraphicSet>
<Para rev:revStatus="R" rev:revHighlight="Update numbering rule">
<?FTID-rev start?>Explanation of structure:
	- The first two digits (XX) indicate the ATA Chapter.
	- The second pair of digits (XX) indicates the Subsystem.
	- The third pair of digits (XX) is the Item Rank.
Item Rank allocation:
	- Item ranks 01-49 correspond to MMEL items.
	- Item ranks 50-99 correspond to Operator's MEL items<?FTID-rev end?></Para>
<Para rev:revStatus="R" rev:revHighlight="Update numbering rule">
<?FTID-rev start?>For example:<?FTID-rev end?></Para>
<Para rev:revStatus="R" rev:revHighlight="Update numbering rule">
<?FTID-rev start?>- MEL item 21-51-01 would be found on page 2.21-51-01.1 in Section 2 is item correspond to MMEL item.<?FTID-rev end?></Para>
<Para rev:revStatus="R" rev:revHighlight="Update numbering rule">
<?FTID-rev start?>- MEL item 11-01-50 would be found on page 2.11-50-01.1 in Section 2 is item correspond to Operator's MEL item.<?FTID-rev end?></Para>
<Para />
<Para>SECTION 3 - CDL</Para>
<Para>This section contains all items from the AFM Appendix CDL.  For ease of use, page numbering uses the CDL item number as follows:</Para>
<GraphicSet id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.GR.0-00-01-00.1675345.0-00-01-00_FAA">
<Illustration fileRef="G0-00-01-00_FAA.fm_1675354" linkRef="URN:X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.NX.GR.0-00-01-00.1675354." />
</GraphicSet>
<Para>For example, CDL item 52-11-01 would be found on page 3.52-11-01.1 in Section 3.</Para>
<Para>When appropriate, illustrations, system effects and performance adjustments follow the CDL item.  The CDL General Limitations information has been printed in this section.</Para>
<Para>SECTION 4 - MISCELLANEOUS</Para>
<Para>This section contains information on the use of annotations for airplane model applicability.</Para>
</FMtopic>
